Aaliadyen of Quellious<br>
Squire in the service of the Church of Divine Light<br>
<br>
/ooc<br>
<br>
I like to duel as much as the next man, but some folks take it to an /ooc extreme, even on this server.  <br>
<br>
I had a Wood Elf Druid named Anders Silverblade grief me for a little bit with constant challenges to duel:  he had to be at least 20th level because he had a last name.  Skeletons are still blue to me, so you can imagine the mismatch between me &amp; my ersatz opponent.<br>
<br>
A little finesse works wonders, though:  I confounded &amp; frustrated him by /snickering &amp; speaking in Erudite.  <br>
<br>
In desperation, he cast a Snare on me (why I don't know; I never accepted the duel), but forgot that city guards frown on dueling:  the Sentinels staff-whooped on his arse until he ran for the teleporter to the High Council building.<br>
<br>
Being griefed on Rallos Zek in my early career left a bad feeling with me, so I have to gauge a person's motivation for dueling me very carefully.  If he is being an /ooc jerkweed, then I'll leave him standing.  If it is RP, then the duel is in good fun &amp; I will accept it.<br>
<br>
If you expect me not to use my spells, you hope in vain.  Quellious gave me my gifts &amp; I will most certainly use them.<br>
